utACK 103f1e8

```
$ ./contrib/devtools/git-subtree-check.sh src/secp256k1
src/secp256k1 in HEAD was last updated to upstream commit c5b32e16c4d2560ce829caf88a413fc06fd83d09 (tree cabf1a0476632c9ac99946c39e663a681cc019ae)
src/secp256k1 in HEAD currently refers to tree cabf1a0476632c9ac99946c39e663a681cc019ae
GOOD
```

Removal of <string.h> include is probably the source of this warning:

```
+In file included from src/secp256k1.c:14:
+./src/ecmult_impl.h:186:9: warning: implicitly declaring library function 'memcpy' with type 'void *(void *, const void *, unsigned long)'
+        memcpy(dst->pre_g, src->pre_g, size);
+        ^
+./src/ecmult_impl.h:186:9: note: include the header <string.h> or explicitly

@paveljanik That's a very nasty warning (being able to use functions without declarations is an ancient C mis-feature, which has resulted is lots of bugs), but indeed that needs to be solved upsteram.\n
Will re-do this now that https://github.com/bitcoin-core/secp256k1/issues/410 is merged\n

```
$ ./contrib/devtools/git-subtree-check.sh src/secp256k1
src/secp256k1 in HEAD was last updated to upstream commit 7a49cacd3937311fcb1cb36b6ba3336fca811991 (tree cfd05e78e0a117016efa89cd75e4ac5a938219cb)
src/secp256k1 in HEAD currently refers to tree cfd05e78e0a117016efa89cd75e4ac5a938219cb
GOOD
```
